results.notes: The provided PDF pages describe the message UBX-NAV-SVINFO (Class ID: 0x01, Message ID: 0x30). The canonical definition is for UBX-NAV-SVIN (Class ID: 0x01, Message ID: 0x3b). These are different messages. Therefore, the canonical message definition for UBX-NAV-SVIN is not present in the provided manual pages.

The canonical message definition is for UBX-NAV-SVIN (0x01 0x3b). The provided PDF manual pages only contain information for UBX-NAV-SVINFO (0x01 0x30). Therefore, the UBX-NAV-SVIN message is not present in this manual context.

The canonical definition perfectly matches the PDF specification for UBX-NAV-SVIN. The only minor differences are the casing of the field names 'meanX', 'meanY', 'meanZ' which are lowercase in the PDF, but camelCase in the canonical. This is a common naming convention difference and does not affect the message structure or interpretation. Scale factors and units are consistent between both sources.
